HEADWORD: Chrysaniline
<hw>Chrys*an"i*line</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>chryso`s</grk> gold + E. <ets>anilene</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A yellow substance obtained as a by-product in
the manufacture of rosaniline. It dyes silk a fine golden-yellow
color.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

